 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search CI/CD Platform Validation Architect Intel 5,432 reviews Santa Clara, CA 95052 Intel 5,432 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Job Company Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description Job Description 
We are seeking a Senior Level CI/CD (Continuous Integration/Continuous Delivery) architect to join our validation team in the Data Platform Group. In this role, you will define and develop new validation capability for our existing products, based on modern CI/CD methodologies, aimed at improving the customer experience. You will interact with Architecture, Design, Silicon Validation, and Product Management teams to research, recommend, specify, and document technology in support of the organization's strategic vision.
 
 
The scope of your role will include: 
Ownership of technical domains end-to-end 
Leading CI/CD efforts to drive a high velocity release cadence at the platform level. 
Partners with delivery groups to roll out best practices for CI/CD across the platform update lifecycle. 
Planning, developing and executing toward vision and goals, including participation in creation of execution plans, driving execution, process documentation, and participating in cross functional task force teams.
 Voice of the team to represent issues found in corresponding forums. 
Works with system architects and domain experts to ensure delivery solutions are program ready 
Role model for the organization and junior engineers. 
Qualifications 
You must possess the minimum qualifications to be initially considered for this position. Preferred qualifications are in addition to the minimum requirements and are considered a plus factor in identifying top candidates. Relevant experience can be obtained through schoolwork, classes and project work, internships, military training, and/or work experience. 
